metadata.name: Pasiphae 01
metadata.description:
Pasiphae

In Greek mythology, Pasiphae was the wife of the king Minos of Crete. She, tired of his infidelity, as punishment, casts a spell on him so that ejaculates scorpions and serpents that kills all of the women he sleeps with. 
These photographs try to represent this story and dialogue about relationships, gender and social truths and lies.
